  "response": "Yes, many Asian college students in the U.S. do eat American delivery food. The dietary preferences of college students can vary widely based on individual tastes, cultural backgrounds, and lifestyle choices. While some Asian students may prefer traditional Asian cuisine, many also enjoy American foods, especially the convenience that delivery options offer. Popular American delivery foods include pizza, burgers, sandwiches, and various fast-food items. In multicultural college environments, it\u2019s common for students to explore a variety of cuisines, including both their own cultural foods and American food.",
